tags.note: The tracks were built in 1953, in order to protect the S. Lorenzo Columns from the trams' vibrations. They were demolished before the Great Jubilee of 2000.
The tracks were built in 1953, in order to protect the S. Lorenzo Columns from the trams' vibrations. They were demolished before the Great Jubilee of 2000.
Proposed conversion of the 90/91 trolleybus line to a tramway line. The project was born in the 1970s, and was neither implemented nor abandoned.

Built in 1927 to replace the former terminus at Via Solari - Via Stendhal; it was replaced in 1940 by a new terminus at Largo Giambellino. The loop stood as a service track until 1975, when it was demolished.
Built in 1940 to replace the former terminus at Via Giambellino - Via Brunelleschi; it was replaced in 1945 by a new terminus at Piazza Tirana, and demolished.

The tracks were built between 1897 and 1904 as a branch from Corso Magenta. This section was demolished in 1918 to extend the line to Via California.

Proposed extension of then line 19 from Piazzale Gambara. Works began on June 2nd 1943 but were halted in August and never resumed. The project would be abandoned after the war, and spare parts for it were used for repairs on the damaged network.
First terminus of Barona. It was built in 1927.
